# [YOUR TEAM] Operating Brain

> The shared CLAUDE.md for the team. Keep this under 200 lines.
> Anything longer goes in topic files linked from here.

---

## Identity

We are [team / company]. We do [thing] for [audience]. Our stack is [list].

## Communication rules

- Direct, conversational, like talking to friends
- Short punchy sentences mixed with longer explanatory ones
- No em dashes anywhere (replace with comma or colon)
- No Oxford commas
- "You" throughout when talking to a reader

## Code rules

- Trunk-based development. No long-lived branches.
- Conventional commits. Co-authored-by Claude is fine, kept on.
- All migrations require a senior reviewer.
- Tests in the same PR as the change. Not "tests in a follow-up."

## Workflow

1. Start every non-trivial task with `/plan`.
2. Use `/research [topic]` for company / market intel.
3. Use `/pr-review [PR-URL]` before requesting a human review.
4. Append to `memory/lessons.md` whenever you correct Claude on something non-obvious.

## Quality bar

- Every section opener should lead with a real example or constraint, not a generic description.
- If Claude is unsure, it should ask. Bias toward asking, not guessing.
- Default to writing no comments in code. Only add when the WHY is non-obvious.

## What NOT to do

- No production-DB writes without a `require-approval.sh` prompt that a human acknowledges.
- No `rm -rf`, no `git push --force`. Hooks will block. Don't argue with them.
- No new MCP added without a CODEOWNERS review on `.mcp.json`.
- No PII in `memory/customers/`. Company names and deal structure only.

## Routing

- Frontend code style: see `.claude/rules/frontend.md`
- Backend code style: see `.claude/rules/backend.md`
- Customer dossiers: `memory/customers/[slug]/profile.md`
- Reusable patterns: `memory/patterns/`
- Templates: `memory/templates/`
- Lessons (append-only): `memory/lessons.md`

## Tools we use (committed in .mcp.json)

- GitHub MCP (read-only)
- Supabase staging MCP (read-only)
- Notion MCP (page-scoped, read content only)
- Linear MCP (read-only)

## When in doubt

Read [docs.heyarnoux.com/teams](https://docs.heyarnoux.com/teams). Then ask a senior teammate.
